description: The TCK 6685 Nuwara Eliya Restaurant at Heritance Tea Factory offers a nostalgic dining experience, set in a beautifully restored railway carriage. The rich burgundy wood and mustard yellow accents pay homage to the carriages historical journey along the tea and railway routes of the early 20th century. This last remnant of a bygone era, now polished and paneled in teak to its original splendor, serves as a unique testament to the intertwined history of tea transportation and railways in the region. The nearby remnants of railway heritage, including an iron bridge and converted station shops at Brookside and Ragala, further evoke the nostalgic charm of this distinctive dining venue.
name: Tck 6685 Restaurant

description: Established in 1841, we have a 174 year-old heritage and trading history. Mackwoods fine tea is produced directly on our own estates . We provide a full range of unblended Single Estate Black Teas in different grades, as well as a full range Flavoured Teas, Infusions and Connoisseurs Teas including Silver Tips and Golden Tips. We are one of the few companies worldwide, who provide Single Estate Unblended Teas in a tea bag form. We are one of the few companies worldwide to be accorded the unique privilege of presenting our Connoisseurs Tea The Queens Golden Jubilee Blend, created to commemorate Her Majestys Golden Jubilee, at Buckingham Palace. We are committed to the environment and we have an extensive programme of replanting and reforestation. Our agro forestry reserves bear ample testimony to this. We are committed to our local community and provide housing, education programmes, crèches, recreation, health and religious facilities. We were deeply priviledged to be graced by the presence of His Royal Highness The Prince of Wales in November 2014

address: 29 Grand Hotel Rd, Nuwara Eliya 22200 Sri Lanka
description: The Hill Club, founded in 1876 by British Planters and still a bastion of exclusivity in Nuwara Eliya, maintains its members-only tradition. For tourists, the Club Restaurant and Bar offer a taste of its storied past, serving as a venue for dining, elegant evening teas, and enjoying drinks. Reservations are recommended for those wishing to partake in these experiences. Evening traditions uphold a charming formality: gentlemen are required to wear jackets and ties for dinner, while ladies are expected to dress smartly, enhancing the atmosphere of refined sophistication. For a more relaxed dining option, the Lilly Restaurant provides a comfortable alternative without sacrificing the Club's distinguished ambiance. The Hill Club combines historical allure with modern hospitality, ensuring a memorable visit for anyone exploring Nuwara Eliya's rich cultural landscape.
name: Hill Club Restaurant
